Trouble: {{.PlayerTrouble}}
{{- end}}
{{- if .PlayerAspects}}
Other Aspects: {{range $i, $a := .PlayerAspects}}{{if $i}}, {{end}}{{$a}}{{end}}
{{- end}}

{{- if .Genre}}
GENRE: {{.Genre}}
{{- end}}

{{- if .Theme}}
OPTIONAL THEME: {{.Theme}}
{{- end}}

Generate a scenario in valid JSON format:

```json
{
  "title": "A short evocative title (2-5 words)",
  "problem": "The big urgent issue that needs to be resolved. Should be open-ended with multiple possible solutions.",
  "story_questions": [
    "Can/Will [character] accomplish [goal]?",
    "Will [consequence] happen before [deadline]?",
    "Can [obstacle] be overcome?"
  ],
  "setting": "A paragraph describing the world/setting context for the scenario",
  "genre": "The genre (Western, Fantasy, Cyberpunk, etc.)"
}
```

FATE CORE SCENARIO GUIDELINES:
1. The problem should be BIG and URGENT - not something that can wait
2. Story questions should be yes/no format, starting with "Can" or "Will"
3. Include 2-4 story questions that add nuance before the final "Can they solve the problem?"
4. Draw from the character's aspects - especially Trouble - to create complications
5. The problem should have no single "right" solution
6. Story questions should shape the plot - different answers lead to different outcomes

Example story questions:
- "Will the sheriff discover the outlaw's true identity?"
- "Can the town be saved before the gang arrives?"
- "Will old rivalries prevent cooperation?"

